author: @diemmy4417
text: It's been so fast that 1 year has passed since the album 'ME' was released. I still remember when Jisoo posted a photo on Instagram with the words 'coming soon', my heart felt very happy and very proud at that time. about her because after 7 years of debuting with BLACKPINK, she found herself a new color and a new direction. At that time, I felt like I wanted to cry. I looked forward every day and every hour to wait for her MV. I remember when the MV was released it was at 11am (Vietnam time is 2 hours later than Korea). I was still studying at school and I hadn't finished school yet. I was waiting for the clock to peak at 11am and I had to watching Jisoo's MV live, the feeling I had at that time now when I think about it, it's still impossible to describe that feeling. I've been waiting for nearly 7 years and today it's been 1 year since the album 'ME' was released. Sometimes I suddenly think that BLACKPINK's Jisoo has already made her solo debut? I couldn't believe it was true until I watched her MV 'FLOWER' again and I believed it was true it wasn't the dream I had been dreaming for so long and finally a few words I want to say To my sister Jisoo, I hope that now and in the future you will always do what you want to do, do what you have spent all your time trying to have a JISOO today, congratulations on the album. 'ME' has turned 1 year old
